---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
import StepList from '../../components/StepList.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Shared setup" description="Install the tools every category needs: VS Code, Git, GitHub CLI, Claude Code.">
  <h1 class="mb-6">Shared Setup</h1>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-8">Four tools make the workflow possible: an editor to read what AI produces, version control to track every change, a platform to host your code and manage PRs, and an AI developer to do the building. Install these once — they work across all categories.</p>

  <!-- 1. VS Code -->
  <h2 class="mb-4 mt-12">1. VS Code</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4"><strong class="text-text">What it is:</strong> A free code editor. You won't write code in it — you'll read what Claude creates and verify it.</p>

  <h4 class="mb-2">Install</h4>
  <StepList steps={[
    { title: "Go to code.visualstudio.com" },
    { title: "Download for your operating system (Mac, Windows, or Linux)" },
    { title: "Install it" },
  ]} />

  <h4 class="mb-2">Verify</h4>
  <CodeBlock terminal copy>{`$ code --version`}</CodeBlock>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-4">You should see a version number.</p>

  <details class="mb-8 border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <summary>Troubleshooting: "command not found: code"</summary>
    <div class="p-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Open VS Code → press Cmd+Shift+P (Mac) or Ctrl+Shift+P (Windows) → type "Shell Command" → click "Install 'code' command in PATH."</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- 2. Git -->
  <h2 class="mb-4 mt-12">2. Git</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4"><strong class="text-text">What it is:</strong> Version control. Every change to every file is tracked. You can always go back.</p>

  <h4 class="mb-2">Install</h4>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><strong>Mac:</strong></p>
  <CodeBlock terminal copy>{`$ git --version`}</CodeBlock>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-4">If Git is installed, you'll see a version number. If not, macOS will prompt you to install Command Line Tools — click Install.</p>

  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><strong>Windows:</strong> Download from <a href="https://git-scm.com/download/win">git-scm.com</a> and run the installer with default settings.</p>

  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><strong>Linux:</strong></p>
  <CodeBlock terminal copy>{`$ sudo apt update && sudo apt install git -y`}</CodeBlock>

  <h4 class="mb-2 mt-4">Configure</h4>
  <CodeBlock terminal copy>{`$ git config --global user.name "Your Name"
$ git config --global user.email "your.email@example.com"`}</CodeBlock>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2">Use the same email as your GitHub account.</p>

  <h4 class="mb-2 mt-4">Verify</h4>
  <CodeBlock terminal copy>{`$ git --version`}</CodeBlock>

  <!-- 3. GitHub Account & CLI -->
  <h2 class="mb-4 mt-12">3. GitHub Account & CLI</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4"><strong class="text-text">What it is:</strong> GitHub stores your code online. The CLI lets you create repos, open PRs, and manage boards from the terminal.</p>

  <h4 class="mb-2">Create a GitHub account</h4>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-4">Go to <a href="https://github.com">github.com</a> and sign up (free).</p>

  <h4 class="mb-2">Install GitHub CLI</h4>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><strong>Mac:</strong></p>
  <CodeBlock terminal copy>{`$ brew install gh`}</CodeBlock>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2">If you don't have Homebrew:</p>
  <CodeBlock terminal copy>{`$ /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"`}</CodeBlock>

  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><strong>Windows:</strong></p>
  <CodeBlock terminal copy>{`$ winget install GitHub.cli`}</CodeBlock>

  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><strong>Linux:</strong></p>
  <CodeBlock terminal copy>{`$ sudo apt install gh -y`}</CodeBlock>

  <h4 class="mb-2 mt-4">Log in</h4>
  <CodeBlock terminal copy>{`$ gh auth login`}</CodeBlock>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2">Choose: GitHub.com → HTTPS → Login with a web browser.</p>

  <h4 class="mb-2 mt-4">Verify</h4>
  <CodeBlock terminal copy>{`$ gh auth status`}</CodeBlock>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-4">Should show "Logged in to github.com."</p>

  <details class="mb-8 border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <summary>Troubleshooting: "gh auth login" hangs or fails</summary>
    <div class="p-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Try: <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono">gh auth login --web</code> to force browser-based authentication.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- 4. Claude Code -->
  <h2 class="mb-4 mt-12">4. Claude Code</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4"><strong class="text-text">What it is:</strong> Your AI developer. You direct it from the terminal — it writes code, creates files, runs tests, and opens pull requests.</p>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4"><strong class="text-text">You need:</strong> A Claude Pro ($20/month) or Max subscription from <a href="https://claude.ai">claude.ai</a>. This gives you access to Claude Code. Note: this is a subscription to claude.ai, not API credits — they're different products.</p>

  <h4 class="mb-2">Install</h4>
  <CodeBlock terminal copy>{`$ npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code`}</CodeBlock>

  <h4 class="mb-2 mt-4">Verify</h4>
  <CodeBlock terminal copy>{`$ claude --version`}</CodeBlock>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-4">When you run <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono">claude</code> for the first time, it will ask you to authenticate through your browser.</p>

  <details class="mb-8 border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <summary>Troubleshooting: "npm install -g" gives permission errors</summary>
    <div class="p-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">On Mac/Linux, run with sudo: <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono">sudo npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code</code></p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- Accounts summary -->
  <h2 class="mb-4 mt-12">Accounts summary</h2>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
    <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
      <thead>
        <tr class="bg-bg-muted">
          <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-semibold border-b border-border">Account</th>
          <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-semibold border-b border-border">Free?</th>
          <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-semibold border-b border-border">Needed for</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr class="border-b border-border">
          <td class="px-4 py-3">GitHub</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text-secondary">Yes</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text-secondary">Every category</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-border bg-bg-subtle">
          <td class="px-4 py-3">Claude (Pro or Max)</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text-secondary">No — subscription</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text-secondary">Every category</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- Verify everything -->
  <h2 class="mb-4 mt-12">Verify everything</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Run these four commands. All should succeed:</p>
  <CodeBlock terminal copy>{`$ code --version
$ git --version
$ gh auth status
$ claude --version`}</CodeBlock>

  <details class="mt-4 mb-8 border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <summary>Troubleshooting: "I'm on Windows and the terminal looks different"</summary>
    <div class="p-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Use Windows Terminal or PowerShell, not Command Prompt (cmd.exe).</p>
    </div>
  </details>
</DocsLayout>
